result.execSummary:
The defendant Kassandra Ann Paulson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kassandra Ann Paulson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kassandra Ann Paulson was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Kassandra Ann Paulson was found guilty of Knowingly Possess Methamphetamine Waste [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.67(2)(a).
  • Kassandra Ann Paulson was found guilty of Possess Methamphetamine Precursors [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.65.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. miscConds.notes:
Defendant is allowed work release privileges for employment and child care.
Commencing 9/30/17 Defendant may be released for 1 month on electronic monitoring for the birth of her child.  (The District Attorney does not object to electronic monitoring.)

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic beverages or nonprescription controlled substances, or any prescription medicine for which the defendant does not have a current prescription.
Defendant shall not enter into any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcoholic beverages.
Defendant shall not have any contact of any kind with Christopher David Winchell (except as allowed by probation agent), Kole Figi, Dennis W. Mason, or Brian Mason.

Pursuant to Sec. 973.015, Wis. Stats., the record of the defendant may be expunged upon a successful completion of probation, and the court making a finding on the record that the person will benefit and society will not be harmed by this disposition.

Defendant shall consent to a reasonable request of a law enforcement officer, based on probable cause, to submit to a breath, blood, saliva, or urine test for purposes of determining the quantity of alcohol or drugs in defendant's breath, blood, saliva, or urine.
Defendant shall participate in any and all counseling deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall abide by all other terms and conditions of probation deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and follow through with all recommendations thereof.

Case called at 2:29 PM.  Defendant Kassandra Ann Paulson in court with attorney Richard Russell Mccue.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Mccue has filed a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form and Plea Agreement with the Court.  Defendant changes her plea from Not Guilty to Guilty on Counts 1, 2, and 3.  Court questions Defendant regarding Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form and her plea change.  Court questions Attorney Mccue regarding Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form, criminal complaint and Defendant's plea change.  Factual Basis stipulated.  State waiving right to jury trial.  Court is satisfied Defendant enters her plea knowingly, freely, voluntarily, and intelligently and will accept her plea of Guilty to Counts 1, 2, and 3 and adjudicate her Guilty on those Counts.  State moves to dismiss counts 4 and 5.  Court does order.  Court will refer case forthwith to DOC for PSI (must be completed within 45 days), additional 60 days for PLEAS, bond will not be revoked.
